  <h2>Bottom line</h2>
  <p>An IDE is the workshop where software gets built: editor, build tools, debugger and integrations in one place, so you write, run and fix code without switching apps. Start with a free, well-supported option like VS Code, lean on the debugger and version control early, and pick a language-specific IDE later if it speeds you up. Next, see <a href="/e/blog/2026-06-14-what-is-git.html">what is Git</a> and <a href="/e/blog/2026-06-14-what-is-an-api.html">what is an API</a>.</p>
